- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses different metrics for node centrality and their performance in identifying core nodes in networks.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with the organization and structure of networks, which can be seen as a system.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with the properties of networks and their centrality metrics.
